	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-39 (134)"/>
			<p>The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-003223">Department</orgName> is already aware that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1036" type="subject">military occupation</term> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/618569/bessarabia.html">Bessarabia</placeName> and northern <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/571096/bukovina.html">Bucovina</placeName> was followed by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-614" type="subject">establishment of Jews in ghettos</term> in the larger
				cities, and that large numbers, particularly from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/618569/bessarabia.html"
					>Bessarabia</placeName>, were gradually <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject"
					>evacuated</term> into the territory lying beyond the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/565888/dniester.html">Dniester
					River</placeName>. These <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">measures</term> were
				carried out under appalling conditions and accompanied by innumerable kinds of frightfulness, including <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbery</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-570" type="subject">starvation</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killings</term> and other brutalities. Only a
				relatively small number of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are believed
				now to be left in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/618569/bessarabia.html">Bessarabia</placeName> – estimates vary from ten to
				thirty thousand out of a total of just over two hundred thousand residing there prior to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1036" type="subject">Russian seizure</term> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/618569/bessarabia.html">Bessarabia</placeName> in <date when="1940-06">June 1940</date> – while in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/571096/bukovina.html">Bucovina</placeName> there are, according to reliable <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, some fifteen to twenty thousand <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> now awaiting <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deportation</term> eastward to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/858911/transnistria.html">Transnistria</placeName> and other parts of the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukraine</placeName>. A great many, undoubtedly tens of thousands, have already
				been thus <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term>.</p>
			<pb n="3" facs="R 6456-39 (135)"/>
			<p>During the past three weeks evidence has been accumulating – first in the form of vague <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumors</term> and unconfirmed reports, then through
				increasingly substantial sources of information and finally in exchange of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-843" type="subject">letters</term> between Marshal <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000010">Antonescu</persName> and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-892" type="subject">head</term> of the local <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term> – that such as remains of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish population</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/571096/bukovina.html">Bucovina </placeName>and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/618569/bessarabia.html">Bessarabia</placeName> is being <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term> eastward into the war-devastated
				territory of the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukraine</placeName> under conditions so appalling that
				they would seem to afford a substantial share of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject"
					>evacuees</term> little chance to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-561" type="subject"
				>survive</term>. Persistent reports have reached me daily regarding these unfortunate <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> – <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, including the old and ill – who,
				given only a few hours notice with the right to take with them only a meager ten kilograms of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">belongings</term> and the equivalent of two dollars in
				money – the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-686" type="subject">stories</term> almost invariably add
				that these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">belongings</term> and the money are taken
				from them en route – have been herded eastward on foot or in carts or box-cars, to war-swept regions where buildings have been razed
				and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> and other <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-833" type="subject">supplies</term> destroyed or removed and where winter
				weather will soon prevail. This modern <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-616" type="subject"
					>Captivity</term> would seem deliberately calculated to serve a program of virtual <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-529" type="subject">extermination</term> and, even if the persistent <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumors</term> that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuees</term> in numberless cases are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">plundered</term> of their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">belongings</term>, that dozens and hundreds are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term> en route, pushed off bridges or dead of
				exhaustion, are greatly exaggerated or untrue, it seems certain that many thousands will perish. Of course, as suggested in the last
				paragraph of my telegram first cited above, many of these reports and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumors</term> are unconfirmed and must be classified
				as hearsay, or even <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-986" type="subject">propaganda</term> by interested
				persons [...] but I am bound to say that even the minimum of truth that I am sure lies in <pb n="4" facs="R 6456-39 (136)"/> these
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-686" type="subject">stories</term> is sufficient to give grave <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-173" type="subject">concern to the civilized world</term>.</p>
